                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origPlace>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100111">France</placeName>
                                    <placeName cert="low" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100064">Paris</placeName>
                                </origPlace>, . The attribution to Paris is based on the prominence of saints associated with the region, notably St Opportuna and her brother St Chrodegang of Séez (<locus from="104r" to="104r" scheme="folios"/>), St Landry of Paris (<locus from="122r" to="122r" scheme="folios"/>), St Marcellus of Paris (<locus from="132r" to="132r" scheme="folios"/>); St Genevieve (<locus from="134v" to="134v" scheme="folios"/>), St Aurea of Paris (<locus from="137r" to="137r" scheme="folios"/>), St Denis of Paris (<locus from="189r" to="189r" scheme="folios"/>), and St Maturinus (<locus from="311r" to="311r" scheme="folios"/>) (see Contents for more local saints). Of these saints particular prominence is given to Sts Opportuna and Chrodegang, St Denis, St Maturinus, as well as to St Catherine.</p>
                            <p/>
                        </origin>
