                        <msContents>
                            <textLang mainLang="la"/>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="1r" to="1v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Table of contents</title>
                                <note>List of rubrics. The last item on the list, St Eustachius, does not seem to be included in the manuscript.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="2ra" to="355vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Legendary</title>
                                <rubric>Incipit uita symonis et iude</rubric>
                                <incipit>Simon itaque chananeus et Iudas zelotes apostoli domini nostri ihesu christi </incipit>
                                <explicit>que conuenerant audire uerbum domini tu autem <sic>Expliuiit</sic> actus <sic>apostorum</sic>
                                </explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        This collection contains circa 100 saints' passions and vitae. It begins with Sts Simon and Jude (28 Oct.) on <locus from="2ra" to="2ra" scheme="folios"/>. The last saint mentioned is the legend of Mary Magdalene and St Maximinus of Aix on <locus from="337ra" to="337ra" scheme="folios"/>.</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        Notable saints:</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="75r" to="77v" scheme="folios"/>: St Germanus of Auxerre (31 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="104r" to="118r" scheme="folios"/>: St Opportuna (22 Apr.) and St Godegrand/Chrodegang of Séez (3 Sep.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="122r" to="123r" scheme="folios"/>: St Landry of Paris (10 June);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="123r" to="129v" scheme="folios"/>: St Catherine (25 Nov.), legend and a short office;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="130r" to="131r" scheme="folios"/>: St Turiaf of Dol (13 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="132r" to="134v" scheme="folios"/>: St Marcellus of Paris (1 Nov.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="134v" to="136v" scheme="folios"/>: St Genevieve (3 Jan.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="137r" to="138r" scheme="folios"/>: St Aurea of Paris (4 Oct.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="139r" to="140r" scheme="folios"/>: St Magloire (24 Oct.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="189r" to="202r" scheme="folios"/>: St Denis of Paris, and Rusticus and Eleutherius (9 Oct.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="239r" to="243r" scheme="folios"/>: St Bathild (30 Jan.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="247v" to="248v" scheme="folios"/>: St Clodoald (7 Sep.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="311r" to="318r" scheme="folios"/>: St Maturinus (Nov. 1), includes vita, readings, translatio;</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        Besides the legends, the manuscript also contains the following texts:</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="18v" to="30r" scheme="folios"/>: Christmas: Bible readings, sermons, homlies;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="86v" to="91v" scheme="folios"/>: Assumption of Mary: homilies;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="98v" to="104r" scheme="folios"/>: Exaltation of the Holy Cross: readings, sermons;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="143v" to="152v" scheme="folios"/>: Dedication of the Church: Bible readings, homilies;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="152v" to="167v" scheme="folios"/>: Revelation;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="167v" to="171r" scheme="folios"/>: Canticles;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="248v" to="259r" scheme="folios"/>: Assumption of Mary: sermons;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="259r" to="270v" scheme="folios"/>: Nativity of Mary: Bible readings, sermons;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="338r" to="355v" scheme="folios"/>: Acts 1:1-16:13 (after which the text ends).</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p/>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                        </msContents>
